---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ChessStats from '../components/chesscom.tsx';
import Strava from "../components/strava.js";
import TriathlonStats from '../components/TriathlonStats.jsx';
import HardcoverStats from '../components/HardcoverStats.jsx';
import ErrorRenderer from "../Error.astro";
import Callout from '../components/Callout.astro';
import TOC from '../components/TOC.astro';
import { Bike, BookOpen, ChessKnight, AudioLines } from "lucide-preact";
import { env } from "cloudflare:workers";

const pageTitle = "Josh Olivier - About";

// Fetch Strava data
let data, error;

try {
  const strava = new Strava(env);
  data = await strava.fetch(); 
} catch (e) {
  error = e instanceof Error ? e.message : String(e);
}
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle} shouldCenterTitle={false} shouldShowTitle={false}>

  <h1>About me</h1>

<hr class="rainbow-hr">

<TOC />

    <h2>Hi, I'm Josh!</h2>

    <Callout type="warning" icon={AudioLines}>
  <span slot="title">
    Hear me <a href="https://www.name-coach.com/joshua-olivier" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">pronounce my name</a>
  </span>
</Callout>

      <p>
        I'm an incoming Psychology PhD student at UC Riverside, and I've spent the last few years working as a lab manager in the 
      <a href="https://fnim.utdallas.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Functional Neuroimaging of Memory Lab</a> at UT Dallas. 
        
   <h2>My research interests</h2>

   <h3>Memory and the brain</h3>

     <p>  
        I'm interested in researching episodic memory, which is the ability to recollect previously experienced events (and which 
        <a href="https://www.science.org/doi/10.1126/science.adn2158" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Endel Tulving</a> 
        famously described as "mental time travel"). 
      </p>

      <p>      
        Specifically, I am interested in using neuroimaging tools like 
        <a href="https://fmri.ucsd.edu/Research/whatisfmri.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">fMRI</a> 
        to investigate how the brain encodes information—or forms memories—in everyday life, 
        how it later retrieves this information, and how mechanisms of encoding and retrieval are affected 
        by aging or disrupted by neurological conditions like Alzheimer's disease.
      </p>

<h3>As a society, we urgently need answers on memory and cognitive decline</h3>

      <p>
        We are in the midst of a rapid global demographic shift, with adults over age 60 projected to comprise 
        <a href="https://www.who.int/news-room/fact-sheets/detail/ageing-and-health" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">nearly a quarter of the world population by 2050</a>.
        Consequently, the prevalence of age-related cognitive decline and neurodegenerative conditions such as Alzheimer's disease is 
        expected to dramatically increase, taking a massive toll on society at the individual, familial, community, and economic levels. 
        </p>

      <p>
        According to a recent 
        <a href="https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/why-we-need-to-invest-in-alzheimers-research-now1/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Scientific American article</a>, 
        the global economic burden of Alzheimer's disease is expected to reach between $10 and $13.5 trillion by 2050, compared to just $2 trillion in 2019.

        There has never been a more urgent time to invest in scientific research aimed at understanding 
        mechanisms and indicators of age-related cognitive decline. 
      </p>

    <h3>Research interest categories</h3>
    <p>
      My overall research interests fall into four related categories:
    <ol>
        <li>The nature of memory and how we can best define and measure it</li>
        <li>How brain structure is related to memory formation and retrieval</li>
        <li>How memory processes change with age across the lifespan</li>
        <li>How neurodegenerative conditions, including Alzheimer's disease, alter memory systems and how we can better detect age-related cognitive decline</li>
      </ol>
    </p>


    <h2>Hobbies and other stuff</h2>
    
    <p>
      Apart from research work, I have a lot of hobbies, including traveling, trying new foods, and learning new skills. 
      I learned Portuguese after spending some time living in 
      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amazonas_(Brazilian_state)" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Amazonas, Brazil</a>, 
      where, I enjoyed eating lots of 
      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tambaqui" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">tambaqui</a>,
      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tacac%C3%A1" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">tacacá</a>, 
      and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A%C3%A7a%C3%AD" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">açaí</a>—some of the best food on Earth. 
      Brazil is also my favorite place to travel, and I try to explore a new region of the country each time I visit.
    </p>

    <p>
      Some of my other hobbies include <a href="/blog/?tag=3Dprinting">tinkering with my 3D printer</a> and doing <a href="/blog/?tag=triathlon">triathlons</a>.
      Throughout my triathlon training in {`${new Date().getFullYear()}`}, I've logged the following distances swimming, biking, 
      and running (according to my data from <a href="https://www.strava.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Strava</a>).
    </p>

<Callout type="info" title={`Swim, bike, and run distances logged in ${new Date().getFullYear()}`} icon={Bike} collapsible>
  <TriathlonStats client:load data={data} error={error} />
  <ErrorRenderer error={error} />
</Callout>

      <p>

        I also love playing online chess, especially speed chess, where time controls are set so each player is allotted a limited amount of time to play their moves.
        Below are my current ratings on <a href="https://www.chess.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Chess.com</a> for three categories of speed chess: 

        <ul>
          <li>
            <span style={{fontWeight: 'bold'}}>bullet</span>{" "} 
            (time controls of less than 3 minutes per player)
          </li>

          <li>
            <span style={{fontWeight: 'bold'}}>blitz</span>{" "} 
            (time controls of less than 10 minutes per player)
          </li>

          <li>
            <span style={{fontWeight: 'bold'}}>rapid</span>{" "}
            (time controls of more than 10 minutes per player)
          </li>
        </ul>
        
      </p>

<Callout type="danger" title="Chess stats" icon={ChessKnight} collapsible>
  <ChessStats client:load />
</Callout>

<p>
  I also enjoy reading. Below is the total number of books I've read in {new Date().getFullYear()}, 
  according to my data from <a href="https://hardcover.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Hardcover</a>,
   as well as my reading goal for the year.
</p>
    
<Callout type="tip" title={`Books read in ${new Date().getFullYear()}`} icon={BookOpen} collapsible>
  <HardcoverStats client:only="preact" />
</Callout>

</BaseLayout>